cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.DL 

This paper deals with the task of automatically extracting structured representations of synthesis procedures from materials science journal articles. This involves natural language processing and information extraction, which are common topics in the sub-fields of computational linguistics (cs.CL), machine learning (cs.LG), information retrieval (cs.IR), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and deep learning (cs.DL). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper.
